The paper deals with session-based recommender systems, which are a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of attention networks (cs.CL) and embeddings (cs.CV) to improve the ranking of recommendations. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of online testing, which is a common practice in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
